'''Mary Tamm''' (born [[22 March]] [[1950]] in [[Dewsbury]], [[West Yorkshire]]) is an [[England|English]] [[actress]] of Estonian descent, perhaps best known for being the first actress to play the character of [[Romana]] in the [[science fiction on television|science fiction television]] series ''[[Doctor Who]]'', opposite [[Tom Baker]] as [[Doctor (Doctor Who)|the Doctor]], from the 1978 - 1979 season known collectively as ''[[The Key to Time]]''.
